Chapter 2 — Cloud Service Models

Cloud computing services are divided into different service models based on how responsibilities are shared between the cloud provider and the customer.




The three primary cloud service models are:

IaaS — Infrastructure as a Service
PaaS — Platform as a Service
SaaS — Software as a Service

Understanding these models is important because they define:

how much control customers have
how much infrastructure management is required
which services are managed by the provider
operational responsibilities
Why Cloud Service Models Exist

Different organizations have different requirements.

Some organizations want:

complete infrastructure control

Others want:

simplified deployments
reduced operational management

Cloud service models provide flexibility based on business and technical needs.

Shared Responsibility Across Service Models

As we move from:

IaaS → PaaS → SaaS

the cloud provider manages more components while the customer manages fewer.

