1. What is DNS
Definition

DNS (Domain Name System) translates human-readable domain names into IP addresses.

Example:

b4n3xus.in
↓
Public IP Address

Humans prefer readable names like:

google.com
amazon.com
b4n3xus.in

but computers communicate using:

142.250.183.14

DNS acts as the translation system between these two.

Real-World Analogy

DNS works like a phonebook.

Example:

Person Name → Phone Number
Website Name → IP Address

Instead of remembering:

142.250.183.14

users simply type:

google.com

DNS finds the corresponding IP address automatically.

Why DNS Is Important

DNS provides:

easier website access
abstraction from changing IPs
scalable internet communication
global application accessibility
load-balanced routing
cloud service integration

Without DNS:

internet usability would become extremely difficult
